  "text": "Chromatin immunoprecipitation assay. Quantitative chromatin immunoprecipitation assay (ChIP) was performed, as previously reported [CITATION_1] , but in this case, with Colo320 and HCT116 cells using either ZFH6 rabbit polyclonal Kaiso antibody or an IgG isotype control. DNA samples were cleaned using a QIAquick PCR purification kit (QIAGEN) using 30 AL for the final elution from the column. Enrichment was calculated by real-time qRT-PCR using an Opticon 2 thermocycler (MJ Research) and primers directed against the promoter regions of CDKN2A, MGMT, and HIC1. For differential enzyme digests, HCT116 chromatin fragments were prepared as above, precleared with 10 AL protein A-sepharose beads (Amersham Pharmacia) for 2 h at 4jC and then incubated overnight with ZFH6 antibody or rabbit preimmune serum. After washing, cross-linking was reversed by incubation with 5 mol/L NaCl ( final concentration, 0.3 mol/L) at 65jC overnight. Then samples were incubated with 2 AL proteinase K (20 mg/mL) for 1 h at 42jC.",
